						               													<description>There Grew A Kingdom is a medieval theme, middleweight strategy board game for 2 to 5 players, and one game takes about 20 minutes per player.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;It is a competitive 4xGame that uses mechanics such as area control, worker placement and resource management.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;It has soft end game trigger, player powers, and card combat system.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The goal of the game is to get the most Glory Points.&amp;#10;Those you get for several actions that reflect the glory of your Kingdom.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The game area is made up of hexagons, which are placed randomly.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;By activating resource areas, you get resources which you are using to build and upgrade the cities, as well as your army.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The army is an important aspect of the game.&amp;#10;It is used to protect your kingdom and expose other players.&amp;#10;Army battles are carried out using army cards.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;This game does not use any dice!&amp;#10;Consequently, the game has a very low luck factor!&amp;#10;Your game is determined by your decisions and the players' reaction to them.&amp;#10;The only luck element is an Army Card Battle that you can try to avoid.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;description from the publisher&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
